entries.definition:
h–th–th to urge, to spur on; to be fast, energetic; agitation;
continuous motion. Of this root, حَثِيث ḥathīth occurs once in the
Qur’an.

حَثِيث ḥathīth [quasi-act. part., used adverbially] swift, brisk
(7:54) يُغْشِي ٱلَّيْلَ ٱلنَّهَارَ يَطْلُبُهُ حَثِيثًا He makes the night cover the day;
going after it swiftly.

